,MrPoopers,2009-05-31T19:04Z,"sn34ky, thivas88, and aexqk, no keygen will allow you to play on Battle.net in the same way that absolutely no hacking program (on a cell phone) will ever let you make cell phone calls using a sim card for which the phone number has been marked as invalid/disabled/whatever.

Battle.net checks your cd key against a list of cd keys that were generated before they began packaging the cd keys.  Cd keys from that list are the the ones that were printed on the stickers on the cd cases, and that list is the one that Battle.net checks against.  That list is stored on their server; ergo, to be able to play on Battle.net without buying a copy of the game means a) accessing Battle.net's servers and finding that list b) generating a cd key that is not already on the list and c) manually adding that key to the list stored on their servers, all without Blizzard noticing.
